==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Parethmoid
<hw>Par*eth"moid</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>para-</ets> + <ets>ethmoid</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>Near or beside the ethmoid bone or cartilage; -- applied especially
to a pair of bones in the nasal region of some fishes, and to the
ethmoturbinals in some higher animals.</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos>
<def>A parethmoid bone.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Paretic</ent>⟦br⟧
